cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI

This paper deals with computerized prescreening of suspicious moles and lesions for malignancy using images captured by standard cameras. This involves accurate detection of lesion's region, i.e., segmentation of an image into two regions as lesion and normal skin. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). 

The paper also involves the use of machine learning algorithms for accurate detection of lesion's region, which falls under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). 

The use of standard cameras for image capture and the low cost and availability of this method suggest that the paper may also fall under the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia). 

The paper involves the use of machine learning algorithms for detection, which suggests that it may also fall under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
